## What We Changed in the Code

### 1. `settings.gradle.kts` — Added Aldebaran's Maven repository
This tells Gradle where to download QiSDK from.

**Added lines:**
```kotlin
maven { url = uri("https://android.aldebaran.com/sdk/maven") }
```

---

### 2. `build.gradle.kts (Module :app)` — Added QiSDK and fixed conflicts

**Added QiSDK dependencies:**
```kotlin
implementation("com.aldebaran:qisdk:1.7.5")
implementation("com.aldebaran:qisdk-design:1.7.5")
```

**Added version conflict fixes** (QiSDK 1.7.5 is old and clashes with newer AndroidX libraries):
```kotlin
configurations.all {
    resolutionStrategy.eachDependency {
        if (requested.group == "androidx.core") useVersion("1.6.0")
        if (requested.group == "androidx.appcompat") useVersion("1.3.1")
        if (requested.group == "androidx.fragment") useVersion("1.3.6")
        if (requested.group == "androidx.activity") useVersion("1.2.4")
        if (requested.group == "androidx.lifecycle") useVersion("2.3.1")
    }
}
```

---

### 3. `gradle-wrapper.properties` — Downgraded Gradle from 9.x to 8.9
QiSDK is not compatible with Gradle 9. We changed:
```
distributionUrl=https\://services.gradle.org/distributions/gradle-8.9-bin.zip
```

---

### 4. `res/values/themes.xml` — Changed the app theme
The default Material3 theme is not supported by QiSDK. We changed:

**Before:**
```xml
parent="Theme.Material3.DayNight.NoActionBar"
```
**After:**
```xml
parent="Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar"
```

---

### 5. `res/layout/activity_main.xml` — Replaced ConstraintLayout
ConstraintLayout caused version conflicts with QiSDK. We replaced the entire layout:

**Before:**
```xml
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout ...>
    <TextView android:text="Hello World!" ... />
</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>
```
**After:**
```xml
<LinearLayout
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:orientation="vertical">
</LinearLayout>
```

---

### 6. `MainActivity.kt` — Replaced standard Activity with RobotActivity
This is the main file where Pepper's behavior is programmed.

**Before (standard Android):**
```kotlin
class MainActivity : AppCompatActivity() {
    override fun onCreate(...) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)
    }
}
```

**After (Pepper/QiSDK):**
```kotlin
class MainActivity : RobotActivity(), RobotLifecycleCallbacks {

    override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: android.os.Bundle?) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
        QiSDK.register(this, this)
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)
    }

    override fun onDestroy() {
        QiSDK.unregister(this, this)
        super.onDestroy()
    }

    override fun onRobotFocusGained(qiContext: QiContext) {
        val say = SayBuilder.with(qiContext)
            .withText("Hello World!")
            .build()
        say.run()
    }

    override fun onRobotFocusLost() {}
    override fun onRobotFocusRefused(reason: String) {}
}
```

**Key changes:**
- `AppCompatActivity()` → `RobotActivity()` — connects app to Pepper
- Added `RobotLifecycleCallbacks` — lets QiSDK notify the app about robot state
- Added `QiSDK.register(this, this)` — starts listening to the robot
- Added `QiSDK.unregister(this, this)` — cleans up when app closes
- Added `onRobotFocusGained` — this is where Pepper speaks using `SayBuilder`

